UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393294900531
KW  - Debt reduction
KW  - Brady plan
KW  - International lending
AB  - We analyze the mechanics of menu-driven debt reduction deals, similar to those recently initiated by debtor countries, in which heterogeneous banks choose freely between selling or retaining their debt claims. We show that menu deals can facilitate discrimination across heterogeneous banks because of imperfections in the secondary market for debt. This implies that menu deals are likely to dominate market buybacks and pure concerted relending agreements, particularly when banks differ widely in their valuation of claims on the debtor.
ER  - 

