UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393294900515
KW  - Business cycles
KW  - Inflation
KW  - Prices
AB  - This paper re-examines the cyclical behavior of prices using postwar quarterly data for the G-7. We confirm recent evidence that the price level is countercyclical. However, we find strong evidence that the inflation rate is procyclical in our sample. Our results show the importance of making a clear distinction between inflation and the cyclical component of the price level when reporting and interpreting stylized facts regarding business cycles.
ER  - 
